# Each subproject has its own .gitignore for its own build artifacts
# (node_modules/, dist/, release/, etc.) - see addon/, companion/, server/.
#
# distribution/ is a build output mirrored from those same projects (the
# packaged addon, the companion .exe, the server's compiled JS) - committing
# it here just duplicates build artifacts already excluded elsewhere, and
# the companion .exe alone is 55MB, which bloats repo history further on
# every rebuild since git can't diff binaries. These get published as
# GitHub Release assets instead (see the project README for the latest
# download link). Keep the hand-authored how-to guides and banner image
# under version control - those aren't build output.
distribution/addon/
distribution/companion/
distribution/server/
